metadata.name: Reverie #237
metadata.description:
Reverie: a state of being pleasantly lost in one's thoughts; a daydream.

I love impressionist paintings of nature, where the visible brushstrokes give a glimpse into the artist‚Äôs process. With this collection I aimed to capture a slice of nature with distinctly digital ‚Äúbrushstrokes‚Äù. Looking closely, you can see many of the lines, curves and polygons that combined to form each Reverie. 

Keyboard Interactions:
[z] Change color / season. There are two seasons, winter and not-winter. Weather (wind, ice) is as unpredictable as it is in nature.
[p] Play / pause. Automatically cycle through colors and seasons.
[s] Save 1000x1000px image (instant)
[2] Save 2000x2000px image (fast)
[4] Save 4000x4000px image (slowish)


Elsif 2022, made with p5js.

metadata.name: REIN #197
metadata.description:
REIN

A generative approach to personal interpretation of reincarnation

It is not my right and job to prove the existence of reincarnation, but the concept makes a good dialogue for my heart and also is a fun challenge for my brain.

1. About the role:

The element on the screen is basically the metaphor for every object/person in your current life.

As the ACTOR, you can make choice under your instant willingness and travel in this world with limited time.

As the OBSERVER you can watch the above and question and dialogue with the ACTOR and alter its choice.

2. About the visualizations:

In order to present our big world in a limited 2D graphical approach. I shrink the dimensions and the detail of the existing reality.

Humans and Objects are dots, 3D entities like us become tiny dots (zero dimension) on a 3D space where their activity is backward translated to 2D perspective coordinates

Interactions between two entities are lines, and in our world planes or shapes were formed when interactions involved multiple people or objects. Which becomes an event.

We now as observer from the higher ground can witness the events‚Äô change, progress, and karma by the continuous growth of the plane into various shapes.

Every world we reincarnated back into will have a visual color and an audio color tone. It is considered to be the theme of that particular life.

The final composition becomes a mix of the above, everything is merely the same but everything yet looks different. Depends on your perspective."

3. Some personal sharing thru creating REIN:

Life is short - I am happy if you are feeling annoyed and you feel the screen comes and fades so fast. Indeed this is my personal feeling about life, too short and things ended before you realize it.

Some life is super long and boring - I am also happy if you felt so. So sing and discover your song of life when you are in the room. It happens once only with this combination.

No time to prepare/predict/prejudge - but you can enjoy cause you/he/she/it/they/we will end in here suddenly. So enjoy the up and down, sweet and sour of every bit.

There is always an intangible target and goal preset to you, and it cast a line between you and it. You can choose to ignore it or be actively chasing it. But no matter which choices you made, your locus was left and shown in front of your eyes.

4. Observer‚Äôs responsibility and award
This work inspires me that in life we can both be the actors/actress and also the observer.

What matters more to you?
The background, your choice, or both?
Are you the observer guy who sits and doesn‚Äôt move?
Are you moving towards the [goal] linking with you? Do you keep chasing it?
Are you caring about the background more? Do you have a feeling they somehow related to you?
Or do you simply move your life freely without caring about the other happening?
Your voice is too loud or not?
Will you find the background noise too loud?
What can you do with it?
If the target connected to you is hollow and empty, would you still care about it?

And Why? Why do you feel so?
Which part of the above dialogue is related to your existing life?
What can we do/change/keep?
What you really can control?"


// [Click] - The sound of the work can be muted by clicking again the screen
// [s] - Take a selfie of this world and you inside
// [spacebar] - you can stop the time and walk/think freely like NEO in the matrix

Behind [REIN]
As a generative artist, I force myself to seek the possible ways to use these tools/skills/presentation forms.

In Traveler, it is about finding the difference between being alone and feeling loneliness
In FEA, it is about possibilities
In BULLET, it is about courage and faith
In REIN, I hope we can treasure what we lost and gained.

Art to me can be the visualization of aesthetics or a mutually enjoyable creative process for you and me.

Or like this time in REIN.

A journey towards our room inside our heart shape box.

metadata.name: Verendelen #35
metadata.description:
Thousands of particles are spread around a group of curves, the general shape of these curves is decided by the hash, but you can influence other things.

This is an interactive and animated piece. You can use the mouse and scroll-wheel on desktop, or touch controls on mobile, to shift the camera around. Because the wrap effect is happening in the screen space not in the world space, you might notice the wrapping makes rotating the scene a little unusual.

Some notes on the parameters:

- The location of a particle can be "wrapped around" in space. The wrapping can be either horizontal or vertical (random), or both (Double wrap checkbox), and you can change the ranges of the wrapping behavior. The Wrap factor param mixes between the original position and the wrapped one.
- The curves can either be a straight line from A to B, or a Bezier curve, the param Line factor decides how much of each.
- Particle spread factor decides how far from the curve the particles can be spread.
- The curves rotate, each at a different speed. You can influence the overall speed multiplier and the axis of rotation.
- If you choose a palette, be aware of the shuffle checkbox. With shuffle turned on any one of the palette colors can be the background, and the rest is for the particles.
- Be careful with the number of particles per curve and the total number of curves. More particles overall means some devices might have a harder time rendering this smoothly.
- Different browser and hardware combinations seem to behave slightly different when it comes to the particle size. If Safari is your main browser, be careful with particle sizes below 20, they seem (almost) invisible!


Made using Three.js and Liam Egan's fxhash-helpers. Their licenses are in fxhash-helpers-license.md and threejs-license.md

2023 - Theo Horsmeier

metadata.name: Geode #116
metadata.description:
A single seed shape is chosen from 13, and placed onto the plane. At every step, a copy of this seed is laid edge-to-edge adjacent to an existing shape, without causing any overlaps. This copy is colored based on the edge it shares with the existing shape. The process continues until the animation completes.

New shapes are placed closest to a moving target. In some mints, this target is slow moving, causing new shapes to expand radially from the seed. In other mints, this target races around, causing new shapes to chase it. 

Each of the 13 shapes forms different patterns under different circumstances. Not all patterns will be explored.

Controls:
  - SPACE: Pause/unpause the animation.
  - ENTER: Skip the animation.
  - R: Restart the animation.

URL Params:
  - "preview=1": Skip the animation.
  - "flex=1": Adapt the boundaries to the size of the window.
  - ‚Äúslow=1‚Äù: Draw only one shape per frame.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Threadbare #78
metadata.description:
Threadbare is a generative art project that explores the beauty that can be found in the everyday wear and tear of textiles. Through the modeling of fabrics and how they respond to being ripped, frayed, and holed, Threadbare creates a representation of the passage of time and the gradual transformation of materials. This project is part of a study by the artist to use generative art to model natural processes and materials.

- You can press [1-9] to resize at multiples of 800 (i.e. 1 = 800x800, 3 = 2400x2400).

- Press [d] to download as a png at anytime.

Created using p5.js

metadata.name: Turtle Vision #38
metadata.description:
## PROJECT DESCRIPTION

What is it like to be a sea turtle in the age of plastic?

Our global addiction to single-use plastic is destroying our marine environment. Over 11 million metric tons of waste plastic enter our oceans every year. Thankfully, there is a growing force of ocean defenders rising to combat this crisis. Activists and non-profit organizations around the world are working diligently to solve the ocean plastic problem ‚Äî but they don‚Äôt have nearly enough resources to succeed. This project aims to help.

Turtle Vision uses code, chaos, and regl.js to offer us a glimpse into the experience of a sea turtle in 2023, struggling to survive in an ailing ocean. Turtles prey heavily on jellyfish, but have trouble distinguishing them from the countless plastic bags clogging our oceans given their similar shapes and movement patterns. Because of this, we are finding more and more sea turtles dead on beaches, having starved to death with bellies full of plastic bags.

We believe that generative art can help to reverse this trend and restore sea turtle populations to pre-plastic levels. Turtle Vision aims to raise money for 5 Gyres, one of the foremost nonprofit groups in the war on single-use plastic. 5 Gyres has a storied pedigree in this space, and has also emerged as a leader amongst conservation organizations in its embrace of blockchain technology.

This project is a collaboration between renowned generative artist @s_r_r_z, the creator of the iconic Generative Octopuses, and @Casson.tez, a professional ocean conservation activist who works at the intersection of environmentalism and web3.

We are grateful for the support of Tender.art, fx(hash), TZAPAC, the Tezos Foundation, and the entire Tezos community.


## EDITION

- Series size: 534 (it's SEA)
- Price: 111-99-77-55-33
- Charity share: 40% of primaries, 5% of secondaries


## TECHNICALS

Visuals:
This artwork portrays jellyfish intermixed with litter in the ocean, such as plastic bags and masks. The outputs offer variance in color, species, clarity, ratio, motion pattern, framing, and additional variables.

Species:
- Moon Jellyfish (Aurelia aurita)
- Crystal Jellyfish (Aequorea victoria)
- Sea Nettle (Chrysaora quinquecirrha)
- Spotted Jellyfish (Phyllorhiza punctata)
- Flower Hat (Olindias formosa)
- Pink Meanie (Drymonema larsoni)

Scenes:
- ‚ÄúDo You Feel Lucky?‚Äù (1 jellyfish + 1 bag)
- ‚ÄúUnwrap Before Eating‚Äù (1 jellyfish + 1 bag)
- ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs In Here Somewhere‚Äù (1 jellyfish + n bags)
- ‚ÄúTwo Bites Left‚Äù (2 jellyfish + n bags)
- ‚ÄúFugu‚Äù (n jellyfish + 1 bag)
- ‚ÄúOmakase‚Äù (n jellyfish + n bags)
- ‚ÄúFeast‚Äù (no trash)
- ‚ÄúFamine‚Äù (trash only)

Controls:
- Drag to rotate
- Hold alt + Drag to pan
- Scroll to zoom
- Press the spacebar to pause/play (in
- Press R to toggle auto-rotation
- Press S to take a screenshot
- Hold the up/down arrow to adjust visibility

The work was made with JavaScript by s_r_r_z_, except for the following:
- regl (MIT License)
- glsl-random by mattdesl (BSD-3-Clause)

- waterCaustics function adapted from jaybird (public domain)
- Compiled using fxhash-boilerplate-webpack by fxhash (MIT License).

metadata.name: coalescence #151
metadata.description:
coalescence is a real-time interactive particle system. Tens of thousands of agents of multiple distinct species interact, cooperate, and compete with one another. Each agent leaves a trail as it moves, and reacts to the trails left behind by other agents, creating complex emergent structures.

Click and drag to erase trails, forcing the agents to rebuild their patterns anew.

Press "s" to save a screenshot.

You can use the url parameter "resolution" to set a fixed simulation resolution, e.g. "?resolution=4096". This can be used to capture high-quality screenshots.

metadata.name: Charcoal Seeds #64
metadata.description:
As a fundamental element derived from organic matter, charcoal happens to be at the core of all life forms. It is also the tool for artists that dates back to the most ancient times. 
By using charcoal as the the primary medium for the exhibition ‚ÄòOrganic Matr‚Äô (and resulting series of physical pieces created in collaboration with Brooklyn-based lab ArtMatr), the works creates bonds between technology and the rawest tool that was touched by the human hand, and highlights how the cycle of life is also the cycle of regeneration of matter.

Since the generative process _that uses programming code and the intervention of randomness_ was used to design the physical pieces, the long-form generative series Charcoal Seeds is a natural way to seamlessly extend back into the digital realm the ideas of matter and physicality, while showing the elements at work in the creation process. 
In each iteration a virtual seed will encapsulates the essence of organic forms and patterns. The graphic style itself tries to convey the organic feeling of tools and materials such as chalk, ink, paintbrushes. 


‚Äî‚Äî 

- "Charcoal Seeds" offers a WYSIWYG experience : by deriving the randomness from the minter‚Äôs wallet address, it is guaranteed that what you see onscreen after adjusting the params will be your actual NFT. 
However, we wanted to allow the possibility of getting some rare features. By selecting "random" for the Format or the Paper color, you will get a chance to mint a Pink or a Back background, or have a Wide Landscape format. Beware : this will break the WYSIWYG ( but it will keep your params settings safe ) 

- As usual, the project is plottable : press [s] in live mode to generate a SVG file suited for pen plotters.

- By adding a ‚Äòscale‚Äô parameter in the live URL, you can generate a higher resolution image. The scale ranges from 1 to 10 with a default value of 3.
